04/07/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH presidency proposed the establishment of joint diplomatic representations with Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro as a way of reducing costs abroad. 
Sources at the presidency said Thursday (3 July) the plan would follow practices of Scandinavian countries.
Also Thursday, a delegation from the Croatian Defence Ministry completed a visit to the military training centre in Banja Luka. 
The inspection, part of a regional arms control agreement, turned up no irregularities.
In other news, the BiH government adopted a book of rules and set up two new committees for economic and domestic policies Thursday. 
The regulations are aimed at improving the work of the state administration and providing better co-ordination among authorities. 
(FENA, SRNA, Onasa, BH Radio 1, BBC - 03/07/03)
